title: Seven-car collision near West Seattle Bridge, person...
text:
One person was critically injured during a multi-car collision near the West Seattle Bridge.
The crash occurred at around 10:00 p.m. on Friday.
Seven cars were involved, and one person suffered critical injuries, according to Seattle fire officials.
All lanes of SB I-5 were blocked. Traffic was backed up by three miles at 11:00 p.m.
Troopers continue to investigate a 7 vehicle, injury collision SB I-5/Spokane St. All lanes remain closed. Unknown ETA for opening.
— Trooper Chris Webb (@wspd2pio) October 3, 2015 One person was trapped and four others suffered minor injuries.
SR 99 or I-405 was suggested by traffic officials as an alternate route.
Traffic backed up by 3 miles -- after collision near W. #Seattle Bridge What we know >> http://t.co/wUiBSkj5OQ pic.twitter.com/UsK6ikG3EN
— KIRO 7 (@KIRO7Seattle) October 3, 2015
